result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathaniel L Bailey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nathaniel L Bailey in court, in custody with attorney James Michael Dickinson.  Daniel A. Necci appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court in session @ 9:02 a.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for sentencing hearing. Court makes record of defendant's plea and maximum penalties. Court has reviewed PSI and alternate PSI. Parties are ready to proceed and respond to Court's questions. DA Necci makes a record that the parties have a joint recommendation, and states the agreement for the record. Response by Atty. Dickinson, who supplements his record as to agreement, sentencing.
9:05 a.m. - The Defendant makes a statement to the Court.
9:07 a.m. - Court makes a record of sentencing factors and finds that agreement is appropriate sentence for this matter. Court adopts agreement and sentences the defendant as follows:
EIGHT YEARS IN WISCONSIN STATE PRISON AS FOLLOWS:
4 (four) years of initial confinement and 4 years of extended supervision, CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE NOW SERVING.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Pay court costs and Department of Corrections Supervision fees
*No weapons
*Obtain and maintain full-time employment
*No drug or alcohol use.
*No association with any drug users or dealers
*No possession of any drug paraphernalia or drug manufacturing equipment, or products
*Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the Department of Corrections

Court goes over voting rights, firearm restrictions, and deportation.
Parties have nothing further. 
Court in recess @ 9:15 a.m.
